"v.使神圣 【考】 反义词: desecrate(亵渎) v. 使神圣 = consecrate 【记】sanct神圣, ify: 神圣化 【参】sanctuary(n 避难所; 圣所) 【反】desecrate(v 亵渎) 【记】源自saint及sacred sanctify (v.)  late 14c., seintefie ""to consecrate,"" from Old French saintefier ""sanctify"" (12c.,  Modern French sanctifier), from Late Latin sanctificare ""to make holy,"" from sanctus ""holy"" (see saint (n.)) + root of facere ""to make"" (see factitious). Form altered in English c.1400 to conform with Latin. Meaning ""to render holy or legitimate by religious sanction"" is from c.1400; transferred sense of ""to render worthy of respect"" is from c.1600. Related: Sanctified; sanctifying."
